<P>
   POLITICS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-CALIF (Del Mar, Calif.) _ ``Conservative'' is collecting
$4.5 million over three days from wealthy Republicans in anonymous
ballrooms. ``Compassionate'' is speaking Spanish on a stage at the
Del Mar Fair while a mariachi band plays ``Vaya Con Dios.'' On his
three-day trip through California, Texas Gov. George W. Bush is
giving an explanation of what it means to be a ``compassionate
conservative.'' By ROBERT SALLADAY.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PARTNERS-AIRLINES (San Francisco) _ The nation's largest air
carriers, with United Airlines in the lead, have appealed a federal
court ruling which upholds key portions of San Francisco's domestic
partners law. By RACHEL GORDON.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-49ERS (San Francisco) _ San Francisco 49ers' co-owner Eddie
DeBartolo, whose dedication to winning and liberal spending
propelled the franchise to five Super Bowl victories, may be
willing to give up the club in a settlement with his estranged
business partner, sources close to both sides say. By SCOTT
WINOKUR.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-PARK (Undated) The take-no-prisoners hysterical
``South Park: Bigger, Longer and Uncut'' has a crafty focus and
ultimately a genius the equivalent of walking into a glass door.
Who knew it was there? By WESLEY MORRIS.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-WEST (Undated) _ Like the '60s TV series that
inspired it, ``Wild Wild West'' counts on a loony premise to carry
it off. It was a spy spoof full of gadgets and attractive women,
which was common enough at the time, but the setting was the
American West, post-Civil War era. By WALTER ADDIEGO.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ My wife formed an exploratory
committee, and we headed to New York. We couldn't decide whether to
vacation upstate or downstate, so we did both. A New York campaign,
even an exploratory one, travels on its stomach, so my wife ate
pizza at John's Pizzeria near Times Square and pastrami at the
Second Avenue deli. She even wore a New York baseball cap _ not a
Yankees or Mets cap, but a cap from the SoHo gourmet store Dean &AMP;
Deluca. That's the New York team Hillary Clinton probably knows
best. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   TEEN-VIOLENCE (San Francisco) _ In the wake of the tragedy at
Columbine High School, it is important that Americans view the
Colorado killings, as well as violence in general, in historical
context. It becomes plain that levels of violence in modern America
are infinitesimal when compared with those of the Western frontier.
By JOHN BOESSENECKER.
</P>
