<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ I suppose I could quit my
job and make our car accident my full-time gig. Or I could marry
Florida's nsurance Commissioner, Bill Nelson. See, the real problem
here is not that a young woman ran a red light three days after
Christmas and sent us flying across the horizon. The real problem
isn't even that she went to court and got the ticket thrown out and
now it's looking like her company doesn't want to pay up. No, the
real problem is that I can't get any answers being nice so now I'm
going to have to get mean. Nastiness, rudeness, obsessive phone
calling _ all of it gets results. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ I gave my granddaughter, Mira, a video of
``The Nutcracker'' ballet for her third birthday a couple of days
ago. Mira is very big on ballet. We watched it together. This
grandfather gig isn't as bad as it's made out to be. (Rosenfeld,
Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
