   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ They don't have stadium seating
and 16 screens, but only at the drive-in can you bellow the Tarzan
yell. Only at the drive-in can you pack the kids in the car in
their PJs. Only at the drive-in can you say what you like without
being shushed. Only at the drive-in can half the family fall asleep
and snore with impunity. The cinemas can be comfortable, luxurious
even, but going to the drive-in can still be an event, an
adventure. (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
