<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ I suppose I could quit my
job and make our car accident my full-time gig. Or I could marry
Florida's nsurance Commissioner, Bill Nelson. See, the real problem
here is not that a young woman ran a red light three days after
Christmas and sent us flying across the horizon. The real problem
isn't even that she went to court and got the ticket thrown out and
now it's looking like her company doesn't want to pay up. No, the
real problem is that I can't get any answers being nice so now I'm
going to have to get mean. Nastiness, rudeness, obsessive phone
calling _ all of it gets results. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ I gave my granddaughter, Mira, a video of
``The Nutcracker'' ballet for her third birthday a couple of days
ago. Mira is very big on ballet. We watched it together. This
grandfather gig isn't as bad as it's made out to be. (Rosenfeld,
Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-ADVISORY _ Cox News Service columnist Joe Murray is on
vacation. His column will resume the week of July 5.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ They don't have stadium seating
and 16 screens, but only at the drive-in can you bellow the Tarzan
yell. Only at the drive-in can you pack the kids in the car in
their PJs. Only at the drive-in can you say what you like without
being shushed. Only at the drive-in can half the family fall asleep
and snore with impunity. The cinemas can be comfortable, luxurious
even, but going to the drive-in can still be an event, an
adventure. (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN-ADVISORY _ John Kelso's humor column will not move
this week.
</P>
<P>
   JEFFERSON-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Columba Bush had the
shopping spree to die for: five days, alone, in Paris. She had
hardly arrived back home in Tallahassee, however, when the press
dealt her the most taxing embarrassment: It announced to the world
how much the little woman had spent shopping. (Jefferson, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
