   COXNET FOOD 0629 _ For more than 100 years, General Mills and
the Pillsbury Co. have grown up in the same Minneapolis
neighborhood, competing and co-existing, with the shared goal of
getting us into the kitchen. And they apparently succeed: Last year
their combined sales totaled more than $15 billion ($9 billion for
Pillsbury; $6 billion for General Mills), about 3 1/2 percent of
all grocery store sales. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
