<P>
   RIBS-CROWD _ If there are lots of people at the cookout, the
only way to feed them ribs off a standard backyard grill is to
precook them and finish them on the grill. But if you've sworn off
parboiling the ribs, what are you going to do? Here are some
suggestions. (Dayton Daily News).
</P>
<P>
   RIBS-REECIPES _ Chefs and grill experts who have been at it for
years put some pretty strange ingredients in their rubs and sauces.
For a backyard celebration when you just want to feed people,
nothing beats basic old-fashioned barbecued ribs. (Dayton Daily
News). 50. MOVED.
