   CELTIC-TIGER (Undated) _ For generations Ireland has served as a
source of cheap labor as starvation, then political unrest pushed
millions across the Atlantic. But lately a boom in high-technology
exports has turned Ireland's economy into the Celtic Tiger. By Ross
Kerber. 1300 words. (f and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-ARTICLES (Undated) _ Northern Light has attracted high
praise from users and e-commerce watchers, and vociferous criticism
from publishers who feel financially threatened by non-subscriber
access to the full text of articles. By Ronald Rosenberg. 1240
words.
</P>
