<P>
   UNDATED _ In his hugely successful cookbook ``A Cowboy in the
Kitchen,'' author and Reata executive chef Grady Spears writes:
``Back when I was punching cows, if you'd told me I was going to be
a chef someday, I would have doubled up in laughter and fallen off
my horse.'' Don't look for Spears to be on horseback any time soon.
By ART CHAPMAN. Story will move in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
