already have some _ about 40,000 doctors belong to various unions,
according to the The New York Times. But when the American Medical
Association voted last week to promote unionization on a national
scale, the 290,000-member doctors' group opened the door to ...
well, it opened the door to a patient's worst nightmare. By BILL
THOMPSON. Story will move in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
