<HEADLINE>
TOWNES VAN ZANDT'S WIFE HELPS HIM LIVE ON IN POSTHUMOUS CD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE FERMAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before he died in January 1997, Townes Van Zandt used to tell
his wife, Jeanene, that he might not have been famous when he was
alive, but that once he passed away she would be ``a very busy
girl.''
</P>
