Housing Secretary Henry Cisneros and his onetime mistress are
``copies of copies'' that could nonetheless be used as evidence
against Cisneros. Bruce Koenig, the government's tape expert, tells
U.S. District Judge Stanley Sporkin that duplicates are usually
entered into evidence when the original recording does not exist.
By GARY MARTIN.
