<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JULY 1
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-SERBS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 29,
about a protest in Yugoslavia against President Slobodan Milosevic
misspelled the surname of an organizer. He is Vladan Batic, not
Babic.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-PAPADOPOULOS-NYT (moved on Sunday, June 27)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of George Papadopoulos sent by the New York Times
on Sunday, June 27, misstated the party affiliation of former
Senator Claiborne Pell of Rhode Island, who criticized the
Papadopoulos Government. He is a Democrat.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-FOSSIL-THEFT-NYT (moved on Monday, June 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 14,
about the theft of fossils from Federal lands referred imprecisely
to the value of relics involved in a court case against David A.
Hutchison, who pleaded guilty to theft of Federal property in
Wyoming. Although prosecutors said the value was $220,813, their
actual value remains in dispute, and for sentencing the amount was
set at $1,000 to $2,000.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PATTERNS-FASHION-NYT (moved on Monday, June 21)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 21,
about an exhibition on mannequins at the Museum of the Fashion
Institute of Technology misidentified the maker of a mannequin
modeled after Dianne Brill and an Asian mannequin. He is Adel
Rootstein, not Pucci.
</P>
</TEXT>
