 &QL; 
KOSOVO-RELIEF _ At the site of a mass execution, where Serbians
allegedly burned to death hundreds of ethnic Albanians, American
relief worker Kevin Cook spotted a human finger charred to the bone
but still wearing a gold wedding band. He calls it the saddest
thing he has seen since returning to Kosovo June 14 as
communications director for World Vision, an international
Christian aid organization. By BARBARA YOST. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL;
