<SLUG> BC-REFORMPARTY-MOVE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VENTURA WANTS REFORM PARTY TO MOVE HEADQUARTERS FROM TEXAS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MAX B. BAKER 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Minnesota Gov. Jesse Ventura, the highest-ranking elected Reform
Party official, wants the party to move its headquarters from Texas
to Florida and away from its founder, Dallas billionaire Ross
Perot.
</P>
<P>
   But Reform Party Chairman Russ Verney .MDNM/said there isn't
much to move because the party basically ``exists in cyberspace.''
The party evolved from Perot's failed presidential bids in 1992 and
1996.
</P>
<P>
   ``All we have in Dallas is my personal presence and a post
office box. We do everything else by Internet site,'' Verney said.
``I guess he's talking about moving a post office box to Florida.''
</P>
<P>
   Ventura suggested the move in a letter to delegates to the
Reform Party's national convention in Dearborn, Mich., scheduled
July 23-25. At the convention, delegates will elect a chairman and
decide on party rules.
</P>
<P>
   Ventura endorsed Jack Gargan .MDNM/of Florida to replace Verney
as chairman.
</P>
<P>
   ``Like me, Mr. Gargan believes party rules should vest power at
the grassroots level ... and create a fair and open playing field
for any candidate who may seek the party's nomination for
president,'' Ventura wrote.
</P>
<P>
   Ventura has said he wouldn't support another Perot presidential
candidacy. In his letter, he said the party ``has declined
dramatically in recent years.''
</P>
<P>
   The Minnesota governor said he will ``remain reluctant to fully
embrace the National Reform Party'' if Gargan is not elected
chairman.
</P>
<P>
   A confidant of Perot's, Verney has headed the Reform movement
since it started as the United We Stand America Party. Verney, who
is a personal consultant to Perot, said he has not decided whether
to seek another term.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've spent seven years at the head of this movement, and my
goal is to bring on leadership to take it to the next level. When
I'm confident we've got to that point, I'll step aside,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
